about.name: Dev Patel
about.intro_para: I'm a passionate full-stack developer with a deep-rooted interest in game development. Currently, I am pursuing my Master of Applied Computer Science at Dalhousie University.

about_me.para1: Hello, I'm Dev, and my early fascination with video games sparked my interest in programming. Pursuing a degree in computer science allowed me to dive deeper into the world of software development.
about_me.para2: I've completed two rewarding internships as a game developer, refining my skills and creativity in crafting immersive gaming experiences.
about_me.para3: Additionally, I've excelled as a full-stack developer, contributing to a range of exciting projects. I also bring experience in working with various cloud platforms, having successfully hosted web apps on both GCP and AWS.

education.institution: The LNM Institute Of Information Technology
education.degree: B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering

work.title: Game Developer Intern
points: Participated in prototyping of 2 game ideas under my mentor.
Worked on a patch update for an already existing game to enhance the graphics and improved the overall efficiency of the game by almost 50%.

work.title: Game Developer Intern
points: Developed a multiplayer game where two players cooperate with each other to cross obstacles and solve puzzles.
Designed the game with a dynamic rope mechanic connecting players and challenging puzzles, emphasizing collaboration and teamwork.
Created and tested multiple working prototypes to fine-tune gameplay mechanics and user interface, enhancing engagement.

projects.description: TuneHub is an immersive music platform that seamlessly integrates with Spotify, offering users an interactive space to discover, curate favorites, and engage with a vibrant community.
Vendor Valley, a web application, revolutionizes vendor selection by seamlessly connecting customers with vendors. Deployment is done using Netlify for frontend and Render for backend.
Developed customer, partner and admin apps as a part of table reservation app tailored for restaurants in Halifax, Nova Scotia. The project is entirely built on a serverless architecture.

A flexible grocery tracking app featuring both serverless and serverful backend structures, along with a clean front-end design. Demonstrated CloudFormation deployment, and implemented an advanced feature for email notifications a day before food expiration
(This) A clean and editable portfolio website with a simplistic design.
Crafted from scratch, a functional replica of the beloved Glitch Garden game offers a customizable single level with adjustable difficulty settings.
An engaging 2D platformer game, featuring diverse levels adorned with traps, enemies, and power-ups. Leveraged Unity tilemap for seamless level creation.
Dive into an immersive rocket steering game where players navigate through dynamic levels, overcoming a myriad of obstacles that test precision and skill.
